title: Zoo Walkthrough 7 — Object Detail by Lamplight
story: friendly-zoo
description: Chained chapter 7 (CP6 rejoin of excluded wt-03-slot-detail). The zoo.story `phrase detail while …:` blocks (Z3b) feed the examine {slot:detail} — the radio's switchable hum via SwitchableTrait.detailWhenOn, the flashlight's on/lit pair via both trait fields. 0/1/N detail clauses. Runs after wt-06 with --chain; the flashlight has been on since wt-04.
---

# --- Back to the Supply Room (the staff gate has stood open since wt-04) ---
> east
[OK: contains "Aviary"]

> east
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

> south
[OK: contains "Supply Room"]

# --- 0 detail: the radio is off; the examine text is clean ---
> examine radio
[OK: contains "battered portable radio"]
[OK: not contains "It hums softly"]

# --- 1 detail: switched on, the radio's detail clause appends ---
> turn on radio
[OK: contains "radio"]

> examine radio
[OK: contains "It hums softly."]

# --- N detail: the flashlight has been on (and lit) since wt-04 ---
> examine flashlight
[OK: contains "heavy-duty yellow flashlight"]
[OK: contains "It clicks faintly as it powers up."]
[OK: contains "A thin beam plays across the floor."]

# --- back to 0: switched off, both clauses gate out ---
> turn off flashlight
[OK: contains "flashlight"]

> examine flashlight
[OK: not contains "It clicks faintly"]
[OK: not contains "thin beam"]
